From: tallman<br/>
<br/>
So we guess it was at least 4 feet. Went to the upper Davidson instead, found it at 3.65 feet at<br/>
6:30p. Got in two runs. What a fun little section! It's roadside &amp; short, much more of a micro<br/>
creek. There are a couple of rapids that might be about class IV: &quot;whale tail&quot; &amp;<br/>
&quot;breakfast, lunch &amp; dinner&quot; the rest of the run is just super continous boogie water.<br/>
Excellent looking water quality, excellent scenery. There were five in our group: me, davidson,<br/>
micklouie, shannon &amp; (a very nice local, originally from Hungary... sorry I forgot your name!)<br/>
~ Great evening on fun water.<br/>
</div>
