<div class='commentinfo comment_'>
2002-09-28 21:06:46 (4263 days ago)
<div id='contact-3277'><span class='name'>mike lewis</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/3277/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Good technical run for creeking. Starts off with a quick drop into a hole,will grab yah but hang on<br/>
will flush out. Next drop scout river right,big rock in middle of river to look out at. Big whale<br/>
tail rock to slide off of,keep right into an eddy to set up for final run. Peal out and hang on for<br/>
a fun river channel run down to bottom. Rest of river good drops. Boat scout, if you want to scout<br/>
can be done on river right.<br/>
Good level 2.0 on gauge on USGS<br/>
Check gauge at bridge at Hwy 280 and entrance to Pisgah Forest.<br/>
<br/>
If you want any more info please feel free to email me.<br/>
micklouie@aol.com<br/>
Mike </div>
</td>
